  "text": "As stated in the General Operational Review of the Infrastructure and Urban Development Department titled \"Addressing the Urban Challenge\" [CITATION_1] , the Bank's urban agenda is increasingly seeking closer links between traditional urban concerns and the macroeconomic investment and policy framework. The shift has been accompanied by a move away from sporadic interventions to encompass broader issues of greater impact for the national economies and the productivity of cities. As a consequence the major research topics in the Urban Development Division are:",
